EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 092300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A DEEP LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IN THE ATLANTIC WILL BE SITUATED
CLOSE TO SW APPROACHES 980. THIS LOW WILL FILL WHILST ERRATICALLY MIGRATING
TOWARD THE BRITISH ISLES MAINLAND TUESDAY ACROSS THE N SEA WEDNESDAY AND
INTO SCANDINAVIA BY THURSDAY. IN THE MEANTIME A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL
EXTEND N FM THE CONTINENT ACROSS N SEA AREAS AROUND 1020 THIS BRIEFLY REPLACED
BY THE AFOREMENTIONED LOW ON WEDNESDAY BEFORE BECMG REINSTATED ON THURSDAY.
THE PARENT HIGH CENTRE WILL MIGRATE TOWARD EERN EUROPE ARRIVING CLOSE TO
BULGARIA 1028 BY THE END OF THE PERIOD. THROUGH WEDNESDAY A DEEP LOW WILL
FORM IN THE NERN WATERS OF THE N ATLANTIC 977 SPAWNING SEVERAL LOW LOBES
ONE OF WHICH MAY APPROACH N ATLANTIC SEA AREAS THROUGH THURSDAY. STRG WINDS
